# Security Baseline

- Always honor the mode semantics from `@docs/spec.md` and `@docs/plan.md`:
  - `local-only` → no external HTTP or cloud LLM calls (`INV-001`, `SAFE-002`).
  - `hybrid` → keyword-only outbound, never full idea text (`INV-002`, `NFR-009`).
  - `cloud-enabled` → only as explicitly configured.
- Never propose hidden or implicit network calls; all endpoints must be explicit and go through ModeGuard.
- Logs must never contain idea text or user content; follow `SAFE-001` and logging rules in `@docs/spec.md` and `@docs/conventions.md`.
- For security-related changes, cross-check:
  - invariants: `INV-*`
  - safety rules: `SAFE-*`
  - tests: `TC-S-*` in `@docs/test-plan.md` and mappings in `@docs/traceability.md`.

